IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: ENSWORTH IS A KINDERGARTEN THROUGH TWELFTH GRADE, COEDUCATIONAL INDEPENDENT SCHOOL.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ENSWORTH SCHOOL (THE SCHOOL), FOUNDED IN 1958, IS A KINDERGARTEN THROUGH TWELFTH GRADE, COEDUCATIONAL INDEPENDENT SCHOOL LOCATED IN NASHVILLE, TENNESSEE. THE MISSION OF THE SCHOOL IS TO PROMOTE ACADEMIC EXCELLENCE AND INSPIRE STUDENTS TO BE INTELLECTUALLY CURIOUS, TO USE THEIR TALENTS TO THE FULLEST, TO BE PEOPLE OF INTEGRITY, AND TO BE CONTRIBUTORS TO SOCIETY.
IRS990.Desc: ENSWORTH IS A K-12 COEDUCATIONAL INDEPENDENT SCHOOL. THE SCHOOL PROMOTES ACADEMIC EXCELLENCE AND INSPIRES STUDENTS TO BE INTELLECTUALLY CURIOUS, TO USE THEIR TALENTS TO THE FULLEST, TO BE PEOPLE OF INTEGRITY AND TO BE CONTRIBUTORS TO SOCIETY.

Form990PartVIISectionAGrp.TitleTxt: ASSOC DIRECTOR OF ADMISSION, HEAD FO

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION DOES NOT HAVE A FOOTNOTE RELATED TO THIS TOPIC WITHIN ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION'S COLLECTION IS CONSIDERED IMMATERIAL FOR FINANCIAL STATEMENT PURPOSES.
THE ORGANIZATION'S COLLECTIONS ARE HELD WITHIN A ROTATING DISPLAY IN THE ARTS BUILDING FOR STUDENTS AND OTHERS ON CAMPUS IN THE BUILDING.

THE SCHOOL IS A QUALIFIED ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE SCHOOL HAS EVALUATED ITS CURRENT TAX POSITIONS AND HAS CONCLUDED THAT AS OF MAY 31, 2022 AND 2021, THE SCHOOL DOES NOT HAVE ANY SIGNIFICANT UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS FOR WHICH A RESERVE WOULD BE CONSIDERED NECESSARY.
THE ORGANIZATION'S WEBSITE STATES THAT THE SCHOOL DOES NOT DISCRIMINATE ON THE BASIS OF RACE, CREED OR RELIGION. ADMISSIONS BROCHURES MAKE SIMILAR STATEMENTS.

STUDENT'S TUITION IS DIRECTLY REDUCED BY SCHOLARSHIP GRANTED. THE SCHOOL AWARDS AID TO WORTHY STUDENTS BASED SOLELY ON FINANCIAL NEED. AN OUTSIDE SERVICE REVIEWS THE APPLICATIONS FOR FINANCIAL AID AND RECOMMENDS THE MAXIMUM AMOUNT OF ASSISTANCE FOR EACH APPLICANT. THE SCHOOL'S FINANCIAL COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE RECOMMENDATIONS AND MAKES THE AWARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES REVIEWS AND SIGNS A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUALLY. WHEN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARISES, THE TRUSTEE IS REQUIRED BOTH TO DISCLOSE FULLY THE CIRCUMSTANCES OF THE CONFLICT TO THE GOVERNANCE COMMITTEE AND TO ABSTAIN FROM PARTICIPATION OR DECISION-MAKING IN CONNECTION WITH ANY TRANSACTION GIVING RISE OR OTHERWISE RELATING TO THE CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
